getFeeTier(address,address).details: Returns the fee tier for a given proxy contract address and proxy deployer address.

documentation.text: @dev Returns the fee tier for a given proxy contract address and proxy deployer address.
@dev TIER_CONTROLLER_ROLE holders can assign tiers to deployer or proxy.
@dev Mapping from proxy contract or proxy deployer address => pricing tier.
@dev Mapping from pricing tier id => Fee Type (lib/FeeType.sol) => FeeInfo

@dev If we want to extend the logic for fee tier placement, we
 could easily points it to a different extension implementation.
@dev Returns the fee tier for a proxy deployer wallet or contract address.

typeDescriptions.typeString: mapping(uint256 => mapping(uint256 => struct TWFee.FeeInfo storage ref))

documentation.text: @dev Returns the fee info for a given module and fee type.
@dev Lets a TIER_CONTROLLER_ROLE holder assign a tier to a proxy deployer.

typeDescriptions.typeString: mapping(uint256 => mapping(uint256 => struct TWFee.FeeInfo storage ref))

documentation.text: @dev Lets the admin set fee bps and recipient for the given pricing tier and fee type.
